# Outbound Exception Exposure Implementation Plan

We will add deep logging filters to our backend proxy services ([JikanProvider.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/providers/JikanProvider.ts), [AnimeService.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/AnimeService.ts), [HomeService.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/HomeService.ts)) and global error boundaries ([errorHandler.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/middleware/errorHandler.ts)) to locate the exact query failure reason on Render deployments.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Proxy Services

#### [MODIFY] [JikanProvider.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/providers/JikanProvider.ts)
- Warp every Jikan method request in a try-catch block.
- Log error details: Axios request URL, query parameters, returned HTTP response status, headers, and the error stack trace.

#### [MODIFY] [AnimeService.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/AnimeService.ts)
- Add exact catch-block prints indicating key cache operations, fetching limits, and deep service resolution error stack traces in [executeWithCache](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/AnimeService.ts#12-40).

#### [MODIFY] [HomeService.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/services/HomeService.ts)
- Add context log outputs on `Promise.allSettled` rejection slots, capturing failure index and exception stack traces.

---

### Security & Error Handling

#### [MODIFY] [errorHandler.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/middleware/errorHandler.ts)
- Update the default `An unexpected error occurred.` generic response payload. During this diagnostic phase, append the real `err.message` and the `err.stack` directly to the JSON response block so that client-side API inspections (or browser agents) can retrieve it instantly.

## Verification Plan

### Automated / Manual Verification
- Compile code using `npm run build`.
- Query localhost backend routes (e.g. `/api/anime/21`) and inspect response payloads/terminal logs to ensure full stack details flow correctly.
